&gt; The same trick can also be used for the other direction to save a division:
NewValue = OldValue &gt;&gt; 3;
This is basically the same as 
NewValue = OldValue &#x2F; 8;
RCT does this trick all the time, and even in its OpenRCT2 version, this syntax hasn’t been changed, since <i>compilers won’t do this optimization for you</i>.<p>(emphasis mine)<p>Not at all true. Assuming the types are such that &gt;&gt; is equivalent to &#x2F;, modern compilers will implement division by a power of two as a shift every single time.

